                </p>
                <p>
                    By the 16th century, Dutch physician Franciscus Sylvius is credited with the creation of "jenever," a juniper-based spirit used for medicinal purposes. Gin gained popularity in England during the late 17th century, particularly after William of Orange, a Dutchman, became King of England.
                </p>
