                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <h3>1600s</h3>
                        <p>Dutch physician Franciscus Sylvius develops "jenever" as a medicinal remedy, laying the foundation for modern gin.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item right">
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <h3>1700s</h3>
                        <p>The infamous "Gin Craze" sweeps through England, leading to social problems and government regulation through various Gin Acts.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item left">
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <h3>1800s</h3>
                        <p>The invention of the column still revolutionizes gin production, leading to the creation of London Dry Gin style.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item right">
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <h3>1900s</h3>
                        <p>Gin becomes a staple in cocktail culture, with classics like the Martini and Gin & Tonic gaining worldwide popularity.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item left">
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <h3>2000s</h3>
